/* =====================================================================
   SEASON 10 (episodes 91-100) — "The Circle" (Spring) — SERIES FINALE
   The wait is over. On a thawing night that turns to sunrise, the town's
   next heart arrives — early for spring, right on time for everyone. Her
   name means hope, and Hanabi paints it across the whole valley in light.
   The town brings everything it has. And at the very end, back up the hill
   where it all began — where the proposal happened, and the wedding, and
   the telling — the story rhymes all the way home to episode one, the town
   lights come on one at a time, the little marshal leads the path, and the
   oldest voice in the story says the last word it's been saying all along.
   The town doesn't repeat itself. It rhymes. Cut to black.
   VOICE RULE: every line must pass the say-it-out-loud test.
   TEACHING RULE: 8 vocab words an episode, each one lived in the story.
   ===================================================================== */

